    "last_activity_date" : 1321899556,
    "last_edit_date" : 1495540496,
    "creation_date" : 1321899556,
    "answer_id" : 8216497,
    "question_id" : 4778113,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>In my case this problem started after eclipse updated the plugin with the v4.0 API release. I fixed it by going to the main preferences for Eclipse and under Android->Build uncheck 'Skip packaging and dexing until export or launch'</p>\n\n<p>Note: if you eclipse gives you the Unknown Command 'crunch' error then <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/7816679/android-unknown-command-crunch\">follow this post</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1254468,
      "reputation" : 11,
      "user_id" : 1214242,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/310d4ef7bc4086984d612650e1bcf0c5?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Daniel",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1214242/daniel"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1329413733,
    "last_edit_date" : 1329413733,
    "creation_date" : 1329408116,
    "answer_id" : 9314579,
    "question_id" : 4778113,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This fixed my problem.  I kept getting the console error in eclipse \"Could not find com_android_vending_licensing.apk\" and even though it didnt seem to effect the way my app ran, it was annoying.  So going into the com_android_vending_licensing project properties and unchecking the \"is library\" option, building the project to produce the needed apk and then going back into the com_android_vending_licensing project properties and re checking the \"is library\" check box fixed the problem.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 188810,
      "reputation" : 34694,
      "user_id" : 427763,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 92,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e7314f6ed3c46d62ce8671cad2c82b97?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "prolink007",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/427763/prolink007"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1334085783,
    "creation_date" : 1334085783,
    "answer_id" : 10095082,
    "question_id" : 4778113,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I was having the same issue as the OP except that all these suggestions did not work. I found a solution for me.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Make sure that \"Skip packaging and dexing until export or launch.\" is selected.</strong></p>\n\n<p>Go to Window -> Preferences -> Android -> Build. Just make sure that option is selected and apply.</p>\n\n<p>I know this does not make a lot of sense, but having it unselected was giving me this error and with it selected it goes away and the apk is installed.</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>I am using the auto generated ant build script from android and ONLY using it as my build process in eclipse. I am not using any other build methods.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1099692,
      "reputation" : 381,
      "user_id" : 1092406,
      "user_type" : "registered",
