  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1803319,
      "reputation" : 31,
      "user_id" : 1641068,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0ebc636f0090e0011047a4e2140f531e?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Mathew",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1641068/mathew"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1347990136,
    "creation_date" : 1347990136,
    "answer_id" : 12482221,
    "question_id" : 4778113,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Find the project's folder in your system, enter it's Properties via context menu and deselect \"Read only\" option. Worked in my case.</p>\n\n<p>This seems to be the source of the problem in many cases, moreover some solutions up there base on copying/rewriting the files in the project what makes them non-read-only.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1899042,
      "reputation" : 11,
      "user_id" : 1715314,
      "user_type" : "unregistered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/7f7037cbb14c0e443929cb1e51427ed3?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Rory",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1715314/rory"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1349216060,
    "last_edit_date" : 1349216060,
    "creation_date" : 1349207590,
    "answer_id" : 12697287,
    "question_id" : 4778113,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This is caused by JAVA_HOME not being set correctly. It can be easily resolved by following <a href=\"http://dotnetmackenzie.blogspot.co.uk/2011/12/android-could-not-find-helloworldapk.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">the steps in this article</a>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 1392599,
        "reputation" : 104,
        "user_id" : 1323041,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/y0JHW.jpg?s=256",
        "display_name" : "wenbo qiu",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1323041/wenbo-qiu"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1373362439,
      "post_id" : 13866284,
      "comment_id" : 25518200,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "1. Clean and rebuild the project 2. Close the project, exit Eclipse, reopen eclipse, reopen the project. Above 2 steps fix my problem, thanks"
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 272449,
        "reputation" : 3669,
        "user_id" : 563535,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 100,
