      "display_name" : "MakingItUp",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1156668/makingitup"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1403188164,
    "last_edit_date" : 1495542377,
    "creation_date" : 1403188164,
    "answer_id" : 24309083,
    "question_id" : 4778113,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Mine was caused by <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/11227335/this-android-sdk-requires-android-developer-toolkit-version-14-0-0-or-above\">this</a> problem (incompatibility between ADT and SDK), and was fixed thus:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Eclipse > Help</li>\n<li>Install New Software</li>\n<li>Add '<a href=\"https://dl-ssl.google.com/android/eclipse/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://dl-ssl.google.com/android/eclipse/</a>' to 'Work With'\nsection and press enter</li>\n<li>After developer tools appears on the list, check it and click Next</li>\n<li>Restart eclipse once download is finished</li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 82414,
      "reputation" : 5117,
      "user_id" : 231740,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 93,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/fEY1c.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Paranoid Android",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/231740/paranoid-android"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1424708843,
    "creation_date" : 1424708843,
    "answer_id" : 28678414,
    "question_id" : 4778113,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I my case, I had to switch from API 21 to API 19, clean and build and everything was fine again. I am using a Mac and apparently API 21 is not fully supported on Yosemite.</p>\n"
  } ],
